==English==

===Etymology===
Old English [[folc]].

===Pronunciation===
*fōk, /fəʊk/, /<tt>f@Uk</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-əʊk|Rhymes: -əʊk]]

===Adjective===
'''folk'''

# of or pertaining to the folk of a land, their [[culture]], [[tradition]] or [[history]]

=== Noun ===
'''folk''' (''plural'' '''folk''' ''or'' '''folks''')

# {{archaic}} a grouping of smaller [[peoples]] or [[tribe]]s as a [[nation]]
# the [[inhabitant]]s of a [[region]] especially the [[native]] inhabitants
# (''plural'', '''folks''') one’s [[relative]]s especially one’s [[parent]]s
# (''plural'') [[people]] in general
# (''plural'') a particular group of people

=== Related terms ===
*[[folksy]]

=== Derived terms ===
*[[folklore]]
*[[folk music]]

